      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Eroded Self</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ken Carlson letter on Jeffrey Rosen's April 30 article on Internet privacy sees how retaliation could get out of hand (S)s</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jeffrey Rosen's chilling article on Internet privacy (April 30) might have gone a step further. There is a real prospect of defensive retaliation, in which we spy on others and assemble dossiers to use in the event that others attempt to discredit us with the dossiers they've assembled. Perhaps this could be an antidote to cybersmearing. Since no one will know who has the goods on us, we'll all have to keep our mouths shut.</p>
        <p>Ken Carlson  New Brunswick, N. J.</p>
      </block>
